## Example 1 — Expressions with Base e

Simplify each expression.

### a. `e^7 * e^-2`

`= e^(7 + (-2)) = e^5`

### b. `(-3e^(2x))^4`

`= (-3)^4 (e^(2x))^4`

`= 81e^(8x)`

### c. `(42e^7) / (14e^5)`

`= 3e^(7 - 5)`

`= 3e^2`

### Watch Out

Use exponent properties before evaluating on a calculator so answers stay exact.

